data.description: Can you imagine living in a cozy quiet neighborhood nestled in between Mountain Shadows Open Space and Pinon Valley Park? Imagine your morning walk, 1.5 blocks from your front door, entering the 4 miles of walking paths in Ute Valley Park, watching the sun rise over Popes Bluff, and turning the mountain range a salmon pink color against Colorado’s much acclaimed blue skies!   Imagine ending each day with a glass of vino, practicing your grill skills as you enjoy the glorious sunsets descending behind the Rocky Mountain Range from your patio- That’s what we like to call “Living in” the Postcard rather than “Looking at” a Postcard view.  Large Pine trees on the back side of the privacy fenced yard & newly planted “Spring Snow Crabapple” trees have been perfectly placed to provide that tucked-in privacy feel while enjoying your large backyard.  These gorgeous trees are showstoppers in the spring, with their abundant white, fragrant blooms in the spring, lime green leaves in the summer, and golden yellow color in the fall! They grow 15-20ft. wide, 2 ft. per year.   This “main level living” home is perched on the edge of Ute Valley Park with its various pup-friendly hiking trails & ponds, and fantastic mountain biking access 2 blocks from your door- Pinion Park Drive/Pine Ridge Trail. Truly a home where experiencing the Colorado Lifestyle is an everyday event.  Fun Facts: Within 3 miles of Your New Home are: Blodgett Peak, Flying W Ranch, Glen Eyrie Castle, Space Foundation Headquarters & Discovery Center, Garden of the Gods (a National Landmark) & Red Leg Brewing Company! Imagine those Fun Facts describing your new nest. Updates that a homeowner might want to make can be purchased in a store - these views and uncommon everyday experiences can’t.  Come Take a Look Inside! Note: This Home is 3 streets west of the D/20 school district boundary line, so District 20 schools could easily be “Choiced” into Rockrimmon Elementary, Eagleview MS & Air Academy HS
